Claims WHAT IS CLAIMED IS: 1. An apparatus comprising: an electrical power cable configured to electrically couple electrical power from a stationary electrical power source to a load at a moveable well construction apparatus; and a plurality of cable guards distributed along the electrical power cable, wherein each of the cable guards has an enclosed interior cross section through which the electrical power cable extends. 2. The apparatus of claim 1 wherein each of the cable guards includes an electrically insulating exterior layer. 3. The apparatus of claim 1 wherein each cable guard is electrically connected to earth ground via a corresponding grounding conductor. 4. The apparatus of claim 1 further comprising a heat conductive material disposed within the enclosed interior cross section of each of the cable guards, wherein: the heat conductive material within each cable guard is in contact with the electrical power cable and the cable guard, and transfers heat from the electrical power cable to the cable guard; the electrical power cable and the cable guards are wound onto a rotatable spool in a manner permitting being unwound from the rotatable spool; the cable guards and the heat conductive materials therein collectively transfer heat to: a resting surface on which unwound ones of the cable guards rest; and ambient air to which exposed surfaces of wound and unwound ones of the cable guards are exposed. 5. The apparatus of claim 1 further comprising: electrically conductive links each mechanically and electrically coupled between a corresponding neighboring pair of the cable guards; and 

 a ground fault detection circuit electrically coupled to the electrically conductive links and the cable guards. 6. The apparatus of claim 1 further comprising a heat conductive material disposed within the enclosed interior cross section of each of the cable guards, wherein: the heat conductive material within each cable guard is in contact with the electrical power cable and the cable guard, and transfers heat from the electrical power cable to the cable guard; the cable guards and the electrical power cable extending therethrough are collectively wound onto a rotatable spool in a manner permitting unwinding from the rotatable spool, wherein such winding forms spiraling layers of the cable guards around the rotatable spool; the cable guards of each layer are oriented in opposing directions relative to the cable guards of adjacent layers; the rotatable spool comprises: a central portion; and opposing flanges extending radially from respective opposing ends of the central portion; and the central portion and/or the opposing flanges each comprise thermally conductive material such that heat generated by the electrical power cable is conducted through at least the heat conductive material of the cable guards and the thermally conductive material of the opposing flanges to ambient air surrounding the spool. 7. The apparatus of claim 1 wherein cable guards and the electrical power cable extending therethough are collectively wound onto a rotatable spool in a manner permitting unwinding from the rotatable spool, and wherein such winding forms spiraling layers of the cable guards around the rotatable spool. 8. A method comprising: reeling an electrical power cable onto a rotatable spool, wherein: the electrical power cable electrically couples electrical power from a stationary electrical power source to a load at a moveable well construction apparatus; 

 the electrical power cable extends through interior cross sections of each of a plurality of cable guards; and the cable guards are reeled onto the spool with the electrical power cable. 9. The method of claim 8 further comprising moving the moveable well construction apparatus nearer the stationary electrical power source, wherein the electrical power cable and some of the cable guards are reeled onto the rotatable spool as the moveable well construction apparatus moves nearer the stationary electrical power source. 10. The method of claim 9 further comprising moving the moveable well construction apparatus farther from the stationary electrical power source, wherein the electrical power cable and some of the cable guards are unreeled from the rotatable spool as the moveable well construction apparatus moves farther from the stationary electrical power source. 11. The method of claim 8 wherein reeling the electrical power cable and the cable guards onto the spool forms successive layers of cable guards such that the cable guards of each successive layer are oriented in opposing directions. 12. The method of claim 11 wherein each of the cable guards comprises a substantially triangular cross-section having a horizontal base and laterally extending sides, wherein the cable guards forming each successive layer are oriented in opposing directions such that at least one of the horizontal bases of the cable guards in a first one of the layers abuts at least one of the horizontal bases of the cable guards in a second one of the layers, and at least one of the laterally extending sides of the cable guards in a third one of the layers abuts at least one of the laterally extending sides of the cable guards in a fourth one of the layers. 13. An apparatus comprising: a first rotatable spool positioned at and affixed to a moveable well construction apparatus at a well site; 

 an electrical power cable at least partially wound on the first rotatable spool and connected to stationary equipment at an end of the electrical power cable distal from the first rotatable spool; a second rotatable spool positioned at the moveable well construction apparatus; and an electrical communication cable at least partially wound on the second rotatable spool and connected to the stationary equipment at an end of the electrical communication cable distal from the second rotatable spool. 14. The apparatus of claim 13 wherein the electrical power cable transfers electrical power from the stationary equipment to the movable well construction apparatus, wherein the movable well construction apparatus comprises a sensor operable to detect an electrical fault associated with the electrical power cable, and wherein the electrical communication cable transmits information indicative of the electrical fault from the movable well construction apparatus to the stationary equipment to stop the transfer of electrical power from the stationary equipment to the movable well construction apparatus. 15. The apparatus of claim 14 wherein the electrical communication cable digitally transmits the information indicative of the electrical fault. 16. The apparatus of claim 13 wherein the stationary equipment comprises: one or more electrical generators; and a transformer having a primary winding and a secondary winding, wherein: the primary winding is electrically coupled to the one or more generators under normal operating conditions; and the secondary winding is electrically coupled to the electrical power cable under the normal operating conditions. 17. The apparatus of claim 13 wherein the electrical power cable transfers electrical power from the stationary equipment to the movable well construction apparatus, wherein the electrical 

 power cable comprises a plurality of electrical conductors, and wherein the apparatus further comprises: an electromagnetic transmitter disposed along one of the plurality of electrical conductors and operable to transmit an electrical signal along the one of the plurality of electrical conductors; and an electromagnetic receiver disposed along the one of the plurality of electrical conductors at a distance from the electromagnetic transmitter and operable to receive the electrical signal, wherein differences between the electrical signal that was transmitted and the electrical signal that was received is indicative of impedance of the one of the plurality of electrical conductors. 18. The apparatus of claim 17 wherein the indicated impedance of the one of the plurality of electrical conductors is indicative of an electrical fault associated with the one of the plurality of electrical conductors. 19. The apparatus of claim 13 wherein the electrical power cable carries a plurality of markers distributed along the length of the electrical power cable, and wherein the plurality of markers visually indicate the electrical power cable when the electrical power cable is unwound from the rotatable spool and disposed along a surface of the wellsite. 20. The apparatus of claim 13 wherein electrical power utilized to move the moveable well construction apparatus relative to the stationary equipment is transmitted from the stationary equipment to the moveable well construction apparatus via the electrical power cable while: the electrical power cable is being wound further onto the first rotatable spool; and the electrical power cable is being unwound from the first rotatable spool reel.
